# Deploying 2048 Game on Amazon EKS using AWS Load Balancer Controller

## Project Overview

This project demonstrates deployment of a containerized 2048 game application on Amazon EKS using Kubernetes. The application is exposed publicly using AWS Application Load Balancer (ALB) through Kubernetes Ingress.

The project also includes configuration of AWS Load Balancer Controller with IAM Roles for Service Accounts (IRSA) and troubleshooting of real-world IAM/OIDC authentication issues.

---

# Tech Stack

- AWS EKS
- Kubernetes
- Docker
- AWS IAM
- AWS ALB Ingress Controller
- eksctl
- kubectl
- Helm
- AWS Fargate

---

# Architecture

```text
User → AWS ALB → Kubernetes Ingress → Service → Pods

